description: Akelius Residential Property AB engages in the operation and management of real estate. The company is headquartered in Stockholm, Stockholm and currently employs 1,265 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2014-06-05. The company purchases, develops, upgrades and manages residential properties. The firm operates in Sweden, Germany, Canada, the United States and France. Its portfolio includes approximately 41 thousand apartments, located in larger cities, such as Toronto, New York, Hamburg, Berlin, Paris, Stockholm and Gothenburg, among others. The firm's policy is based on the cherry picking strategy, comprising small purchases of apartments with renovation potential, located in developing cities, districts and suburbs; the upgrade of rental apartments to First Class, the standard level of newly built flats; and the sale of turnkey properties. The firm is a parent entity of the Akelius Fastigheter group.
